âœ… What is an Attribute in HTML?
An attribute provides additional information or properties about an HTML element.
Attributes are always written inside the opening tag and usually come in nameâ€“value pairs.

ğŸ”¹ Example => <img src="photo.jpg" alt="Profile Image">
src â†’ specifies image source
